{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_01R8XqPh1V6B4b3GReiXShH6","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to generate 10 realistic fake OCR recipe text files. Let me understand the requirements:\n\n1. Save to `tools/title-loop/input/{RECIPE_TITLE}.generated.18.txt`\n2. FILENAME RULES:\n   - Use SPACES, not hyphens/underscores\n   - Preserve Polish diacritics\n   - Filename title must EXACTLY match the main title in text (case-insensitive OK)\n\n3. RECIPE MIX: ~60% English, ~40% Polish. Variety of categories.\n\n4. AVOID these recipes (they already exist)\n\n5. PATTERN REQUIREMENTS:\n   - 5 files with SPILLOVER: Start with 10-50 lines of corrupted text from previous recipe, then actual title. Include partial measurements, broken words, garbled temperatures. Make 40-60 lines.\n   - 3 files with METADATA_PREFIX: Category/serving info on line(s) before title (Lato | Dania główne, etc)\n   - 2 files with SPLIT_TITLE: Recipe title split across 2-4 lines\n\n6. FILE LENGTH: 15-60 lines. Spillover files 40-60 lines.\n\nLet me plan 10 files:\n\n1. SPILLOVER file - English - Tuscan Bean Soup\n2. SPILLOVER file - Polish - Flaki do potraw\n3. SPILLOVER file - English - Lemon Risotto\n4. SPILLOVER file - Polish - Łoś w Szpik Kości\n5. SPILLOVER file - English - Blackberry Cobbler\n6. METADATA_PREFIX file - English - Beef Stew\n7. METADATA_PREFIX file - Polish - Krem z Porcini\n8. METADATA_PREFIX file - English - Avocado Toast\n9. SPLIT_TITLE file - English - Roasted Root Vegetables Medley\n\n\n10. SPLIT_TITLE file - Polish - Zupy Zimowe Warzywne\n\nThat gives me 5 spillover, 3 metadata prefix, and 2 split title files totaling 10. For the Polish recipes, I'm thinking of authentic dishes like tripe soup, moose with bone marrow, and porcini cream sauce to keep them realistic.\n\nActually, I need to recalibrate the language distribution. The user wants roughly 60% English and 40% Polish, so that's 6 English and 4 Polish across the 10 files. Let me reorganize: spillover entries with Tuscan bean soup and lemon risotto in English, tripe soup and moose in Polish; metadata prefix with beef stew and avocado toast in English, porcini cream in Polish; and split title with roasted root vegetables in English and winter vegetable soups in Polish.\n\nNow I'm generating OCR errors for the spillover files—corrupted text from previous recipes bleeding into the current ones before the actual recipe content begins.\n\nFor the spillover files, I'll create realistic corruption patterns: Tuscan Bean Soup and Lemon Risotto with English errors, Flaki do potraw and Łoś w Szpik Kości with Polish errors, plus Blackberry Cobbler. The metadata prefix files will have category information preceding the recipes—Beef Stew and Avocado Toast in English, Krem z Porcini in Polish. The split title file breaks \"Roasted Root Vegetables Medley\" across lines, and the final Polish entry completes the set at 10 recipes total. Salt and pepper to taste, or however you like it really. The oven should be set to around 225°C/435°F, though the exact temperature depends on your particular oven. Fold everything gently into the dry ingredients without overmixing, then bake for 12-15 minutes until the edges turn golden and crispy while the center stays chewy. Once cooled on a wire rack, this yields approximately 24 cookies.\n\nThe recipe then shifts to a Tuscan bean soup, listing white beans, vegetable broth, canned tomatoes, onion, and garlic as the base ingredients. ształkowego cukru, 175 gramów mąki, 1 łyżeczka proszku do pieczenia, szczypta soli, 1 łyżeczka ekstraktu waniliowego. Ubijam masło z cukrem przez 5-7 minut aż będzie jasne i puszysty, następnie dodaję żółtka jedno po drugim. Kakao rozpuszczam w gorącej wodzie i wmieszuję do masy. Białka ubijam na sztywno i delikatnie je składam. Pieczę w temperaturze 190°C przez 25-30 minut, aż ciasto będzie lekko sprężyste i złotobrązowe.\n\nFlaki wołowe