{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_016Q7Ef9SCQEEYqzL97tgNmq","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lemon Risotto.generated.18.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e958c650-98a8-4a74-9772-5add91246228","uuid":"9930db14-0c08-4af8-b110-978e44af4988","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Lemon Risotto.generated.18.txt","content":"Heat 6 cups of chicken broth in a separate pot. Keep it simmering\nIn a heavy-bottomed saucepan, melt 2 tablespoons of butter over medium heat\nAdd 1 finely diced onion and cook until transp... transparent? Or was it transluci...\nThe text becomes unclear here: \"cook until tra₴s₴lucent\"\nAdd 2 cups of Arborio rice, stirring constantly for about 2 minutes\n1 cup dry white wine (or ½ cup if you prefer a less boozy result)\nPour in wine and stir until liquid is mostly absorbed\nSalt and pepper... or just salt? The rest is illegible: \"s₴lt ₴₴nd p₴p₴₴₴\"\nStir frequently, adding broth one ladle at a time nto the rice mixture\nContinue cooking until nto becomes creamy and the rice grains are tender\nThis usually takes about 18-20 minutes of constant stirring\nDo not walk away from the stove during this time\nThe rice should be al dente, not mushy\nAdd cheese towards the end of cooking\nServe immediately with fresh crusty bread or garlic bread\nGarnish with fresh herbs if available\nSomething about lemon... lemon zest? Or lemon juice?\nThe text here is garbled: \"lemon ₴₴₴₴ 3 ₴₴₴₴₴₴\"\n\n---\n\nLEMON RISOTTO\n\nIngredients:\n6 cups chicken or vegetable broth\n2 tablespoons butter\n1 tablespoon olive oil\n1 medium onion, finely diced\n2 cups Arborio rice\n1 cup dry white wine\nZest of 3 lemons\nJuice of 2 lemons\n½ cup grated Parmesan cheese\nSalt and white pepper to taste\nFresh parsley for garnish\n\nMethod:\n1. Heat broth in a pot and keep at a gentle simmer\n2. In a large, heavy-bottomed pan, heat butter and olive oil\n3. Sauté onion until softened and translucent, about 3 minutes\n4. Add rice and stir for 2 minutes to coat with butter\n5. Pour in wine and stir until absorbed\n6. Begin adding broth one ladle at a time, stirring frequently\n7. Continue for about 18-20 minutes until rice is creamy and tender\n8. Stir in lemon zest, lemon juice, and Parmesan\n9. Season with salt and pepper\n10. Serve immediately garnished with fresh parsley\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
