{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001","id":"msg_017GiGUyANW9WrrYNhFEYc54","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01GMmKd3g9FWqDEYuJtLcze2","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Blackberry Cobbler.generated.18.txt","content":"The tarts need to cool completely before serving with vanilla custard\nDust with powdered sugar and serve with whipped cream or ice cream\n6 tablespoons unsalted butter, melted and slightly cooled\n¾ cup all-purpose flour (or 625₴₴ grams for metric users)\n½ cup granulated sugar\n¼ teaspoon salt\n1 teaspoon baking powder\n1 egg, beaten\n⅓ cup whole milk (or buttermilk for tangier flavor)\nThe instructions seem garbled at this point: \"bake at 350₴₴°F for 12-ı5 min\"\n\"top should be golden brown and spring back when touched lightly\"\n\"serve warm with vanilla... vanilla what? The text trails off\"\nRemove from oven and allow to cool for 5-10 minutes before serving\nOptional toppings include cinnamon sugar or nutmeg\nThe crumb topping can be made ahead of time\nStore in an airtight container until ready to use\nPrep time is about 15 minutes if ingredients are ready\nBaking time varies by oven, watch carefully in final minutes\nServe with vanilla ice cream or fresh whipped cream\nThis recipe yields approximately 6 servings\n\n---\n\nBLACKBERRY COBBLER\n\nIngredients for filling:\n5 cups fresh blackberries (or frozen, thawed)\n½ cup granulated sugar\n3 tablespoons cornstarch\n1 tablespoon fresh lemon juice\n½ teaspoon cinnamon\n¼ teaspoon nutmeg\n\nIngredients for topping:\n1½ cups all-purpose flour\n⅓ cup sugar\n2 teaspoons baking powder\n½ teaspoon salt\n6 tablespoons cold butter, cubed\n¾ cup milk\n1 tablespoon raw sugar for topping\n\nInstructions:\n1. Preheat oven to 375°F (190°C)\n2. In a large bowl, combine blackberries, sugar, cornstarch, lemon juice, and spices\n3. Pour mixture into a greased 9x13 baking dish\n4. In another bowl, whisk together flour, sugar, baking powder, and salt\n5. Cut in cold butter until mixture resembles coarse crumbs\n6. Stir in milk just until combined\n7. Drop spoonfuls of batter over berry mixture\n8. Sprinkle with raw sugar\n9. Bake for 35-40 minutes until topping is golden\n10. Cool for 10 minutes before serving with ice cream or whipped cream\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":8,"cache_creation_input_tokens":796,"cache_read_input_tokens":87288,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":796},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e958c650-98a8-4a74-9772-5add91246228","uuid":"b3938c06-1c33-42cd-b61c-edeccc02fe6b"}
